Subject: config: add host-side default_scale_factor so user sets it once

Apollo's existing scale_factor flow (before this patch):

  1. Moonlight client URL arg `scaleFactor=N` → launch_session->scale_factor
     (defaults to 100 — most moonlight clients never pass this)
  2. apps.json per-app `scale-factor` field → overrides launch_session
     value if != 100
  3. process.cpp uses whichever survives

Result: there is NO host-side way to say "use 150% for every game I have
configured." The user has to edit each app's scale-factor individually,
and a newly added app starts at 100 (the editForm default). User
feedback:

  "i dont like that i have to set the resolution to the max i set on the
   scale factor every game, i would like that it auto uses the maximum
   one"

This patch adds a host config field `default_scale_factor` (config.h
video_t, registered in config.cpp at the same precedence level as `qp`,
`hevc_mode`, etc.). Reading order in process.cpp becomes:

   1. apps.json per-app scale-factor (if != 100)    — highest priority
   2. client URL scaleFactor (if != 100)
   3. host config default_scale_factor               — NEW global default
   4. 100 (no scaling)                              — fallback

User sets `default_scale_factor = 150` in `~/.config/sunshine/sunshine.conf`
once, every game now renders at 1.5x resolution and downsamples to the
client. Per-app overrides still work for anything they want different.

Validated range 20-200% (matches the web UI slider patch 0010 enabled).
Default value 100 keeps existing behaviour for everyone who doesn't set
it. Backwards-compatible.

This patch deliberately does NOT add a web UI input — `sunshine.conf`
is the supported config path and the existing per-app slider already
exists for game-specific tweaks. Adding a global UI control would
require Vue + confighttp.cpp + i18n locale changes for marginal value.

--- a/src/config.h
+++ b/src/config.h
@@ -31,6 +31,13 @@
 
     int min_threads;  // Minimum number of threads/slices for CPU encoding
 
+    // Host-side default resolution scale factor applied when neither the
+    // client nor the per-app config requested anything else. Percentage,
+    // 100 = unchanged. Lets the user set ONE number here and have it
+    // apply to every app, instead of editing each app's scale-factor
+    // field individually. Per-app values != 100 still win.
+    int default_scale_factor;
+
     struct {
       std::string sw_preset;
       std::string sw_tune;
--- a/src/config.cpp
+++ b/src/config.cpp
@@ -447,6 +447,9 @@
     0,  // av1_mode
 
     2,  // min_threads
+
+    100,  // default_scale_factor (100 = no host-side scaling; per-app override still applies)
+
     {
       "superfast"s,  // preset
       "zerolatency"s,  // tune
@@ -1111,6 +1114,7 @@
